                  <scopecontent>
                     <p>Transcript in an unidentified hand, headed "&amp; Where is this
								Epitaph", in a volume entitled <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Memorials of
								Richard Gough</title>, volume II, section I. "Poems preserved by 
								Richard Gough Esq.". The volume, which is 14 5/8 x
								9 3/4 in. in size and contains 320 leaves, is one of two Volumes of Poems
								and other interesting Memorials of Richard Gough, Esq., F.R.S., F.S.A..,
								collected by J[ohn] B[owyer] Nichols (<extref href="https://databank.ora.ox.ac.uk/misccoll/datasets/SumCatV6/summary_catalogue_vol_VI.pdf"
                                show="new"
                                linktype="simple">
                           <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Summary Catalogue</title>
                        </extref>, 32551).</p>
